programmes.show_description: International Intrigue. Guy Fieri traverses the US, grabbing international eats from Thai in Texas to Ethiopian in Arizona. And, he visits a Latin place serving empanadas in Miami. S28, Ep6
Lights-Out Latin. Guy checks out amazing Latin specialities from Peruvian sandwiches in Miami T Panama flavours in North Carolina to a joint in Arizona serving tacos and carne asada. S28, Ep7
Detroit. Adam Richman visits Detroit, Michigan for the massive Triple Threat Pork sandwich, two duelling Coney Dog joints, and the world's biggest burger! S2, Ep15
Philadelphia. Adam heads to Philadelphia, Pennsylvania for an Italian roast pork sandwich, a mega ice cream concoction known as Mt. Vesuvius, and the Ultimate Cheesesteak Challenge. S2, Ep17
Pizza, Pooches & Pop-In-Law. Buddy makes a canine friend when he is asked to make a cake for an animal shelter. He also challenges his father-in-law to a pizza making contest. S2, Ep4
Children, a Cage, and a Challenge. As well as producing an innovative talking cake for a children's museum, Buddy is tasked with making a cage fighting cake. S2, Ep5

Devon. The next leg of James's trip sees him in Devon, joined by Michelin-starred chef, Simon Hulstone. They check out delicious local mushrooms and cheeses. S1, Ep3
The Bikers cross Arizona in search of the Wild West. They visit Monument Valley and are invited to a traditional Navajo BBQ. Plus, they meet the man who saved Route 66. S1, Ep5
Brunch Bites. Ree Drummond serves up effortless brunch ideas. She takes four favourites to the next level, from a leftover frittata sandwich board to a crispy A.M. wrap. S26, Ep4
A Little Healthier. Ree shakes up well-loved recipes and makes them a bit healthier. She puts a spin on the family's takeaway favourite and skips the crust for her classic apple pie. S26, Ep5
Noodle Broth And Veggie Chilli. On the menu this time is squid 'n' prawns spicy vegetable noodle broth. Plus, veggie chilli with crunchy tortilla and avocado salad. S1, Ep37
Asian Fish And Ultimate Pork Tacos. Jamie shows how to make Asian fish, miso noodles and crunchy veg. Plus, the ultimate pork tacos, spicy black beans and avocado garden salad. S1, Ep38
Birthday Parties. Ina Garten goes back to basics for husband Jeffrey's birthday. She makes a nostalgic dinner of matzo balls, chicken soup and fillet of beef with gorgonzola sauce. S3, Ep1
Tex-Mex. Ina Garten makes a Tex-Mex meal with her friend Devon Fredericks and her award-winning chilli recipe. Side dishes include tequila lime chicken and guacamole. S3, Ep2
Biscuit Week. The bakers make personalised signature biscuits, which must be about a place in the British Isles. Then, there's an iconic technical and a spectacular 3D Showstopper. S9, Ep1
Cake Week. The 11 remaining are tested with a crowd-pleasing signature challenge, Prue's first technical challenge, and a chocolate collared Showstopper. S9, Ep2
James Martin is in Hampshire to learn about the process of growing watercress. Back in the kitchen, he makes scallop salad, stilton soup and a red onion pizza. S1, Ep7
Chef James Martin is in Mudeford Quay to search for fresh fish. Later, he demonstrates how to make brill with boudin, halibut parcels and shrimp butter. S1, Ep8
Chef James Martin picks up some fresh rhubarb from a huge farm in Salisbury. Then, he makes a rhubarb crumble with a twist and a plum chutney. S1, Ep9
Chef James Martin visits a peculiar farm in the Hampshire Downs. Then, he returns to the kitchen to cook three delicious meals with mozzarella. S1, Ep10

Boise, ID. Casey Webb is in Boise, Idaho to sample their burger celebrations and potato innovations. Plus, he takes on a diabolically spicy challenge known as Demon's Delight. S2, Ep11
Grand Rapids, MI. Casey Webb visits Grand Rapids in Michigan, a city famous for its beer, to indulge in a hot dish, a saucy burrito and a five-pound chilli dog challenge. S2, Ep12
So Sous Me. Brian Goodman is laying claim to Jonathan Sawyer's James Beard Award, and De'Unaka Haley is battling to earn Niema DiGrazia's trust. S1, Ep4
Pizza, Pork And Peru. Guy digs into pizza with a surprise in Lansing, MI, standout Philly sandwiches in Wilmington, NC, and authentic Peruvian specialities in Tucson, AZ. S28, Ep8
Seafood And Savory. Guy checks out a Bosnian restaurant in Tucson, AZ, serving up Eastern European specialities to a place frying favourites in Wilmington, NC. S28, Ep9
Grab And Grub. Guy grabs all kinds of grub, including a Chicago-style spot in Tucson, AZ, serving deep-dish pie. In Miami, NFL coach Jon Gruden joins him to check out a Cuban place. S28, Ep10
BBQ Bites And Southern Flavor. Guy visits a Seattle barbecue joint serving up ribs and brisket chilli, and a Southern spot in California specialising in fried chicken and collards. S28, Ep11
Tucson. Adam Richman visits Tucson, Arizona for a hot dog wrapped in bacon and covered in all the trimmings, a huge platter of Mexican eats and the massive O.M.G Burger Challenge. S2, Ep18
New Brunswick, NJ. Adam heads to New Brunswick, New Jersey, for huge triple-decker deli sandwiches, two-pound Stromboli, and the legendary Fat Sandwich Challenge at a grease truck. S2, Ep19
Golf Greens & Gravity. The boys go golfing to get inspiration for a golf tournament cake and feel lost in space whilst creating a cake for a local planetarium. S2, Ep7
Freaks, Fast Food & Frightened Frankie. The bakery heavyweights are challenged to an eating contest and one of Frankie's biggest fears is exposed whilst making a complicated cake. S2, Ep8

Eating Up New Orleans. Guy Fieri is taking a tasty tour of New Orleans, Louisiana. He stops at a seafood restaurant that serves up creative dishes and tries potato salad with a twist. S29, Ep13
Belly, Beef And Bratwurst. Guy Fieri is in Atlanta to visit an Asian eatery that serves up pork belly and wok-fried chicken. Then, a diner in Vancouver dishes out duck pancakes. S29, Ep17
Mom's Kitchen. Guy hits the road for grub with a maternal touch. In Boulder, a mother-son team serves up Chinese specialties. In Columbus, a Jamaican joint dishes out jerk chicken. S28, Ep1
Rollin' In The Dough. Guy Fieri digs into dishes featuring dynamite dough. He checks out meaty buns at a Hawaiian joint in Arizona, and a shop in Miami making artisan doughnuts. S28, Ep5
Chicken 101. Ina outlines some simple and easy recipes for delicious roast chicken, curried chicken salad and two delicious chicken shortcuts. Plus, she answers some fan questions. S2, Ep13
Farm Stand Food. From one box of supplies from a local farm, Ina creates three farm fresh dishes: scalloped tomatoes, cape cod chopped salad and zucchini pancakes. S2, Ep14
Get Grilling. From grilled Indonesian swordfish packed with flavour to a BBQ skirt steak recipe from chef Joe Realmuto, Ina has some simple grilling recipes for any occasion. S2, Ep15
Baking Basics. Local baker Kathleen King shares recipes for double chocolate almond cookies, an easy-bake Irish Soda Bread and an easy shortcut for savoury palmiers. S2, Ep16
Italian Restaurant Food At Home. This time, Italian restaurant quality food at home. Chef Joe Realmuto shares his recipes for penne alla Vecchia Bettola and rum raisin tiramisu. S2, Ep17
Surprise, Surprise. Ina prepares lasagne with a Greek twist and serves it with an arugula and watermelon feta salad for a surprise dinner date with Jeffrey. S2, Ep18
Chill Out. Nadiya has some relaxed recipes to chill out with, including Bombay burgers, sticky BBQ sriracha chicken and a dreamy apple and custard pie. S1, Ep5
Special Occasions. Nadiya shares her celebratory recipes for special occasions. Roast leg of lamb makes a fabulous party centrepiece along with lemon drizzle swirls. S1, Ep6
Impress In An Instant. Nadiya shares time-saving recipes to take the stress out of impressing guests. She makes raspberry cheesecake croissants and satay chicken tray bake. S1, Ep5
Sweet & Easy. Nadiya shares her favourite recipes for something sweet, delicious, and deceptively simple. They include a giant time-saving cookie and a nutty baklava. S1, Ep6
James visits the Dordogne, known for its hearty cuisine. He tastes three local specialities and seeks out the region's local icon, black truffle! S1, Ep5
James travels to Lyon to explore two sides of the culinary scene. He visits the city's famous food market and experiences fine-dining at Michelin-starred restaurants. S1, Ep6
On a trip to Ireland, Mary is thrilled to explore a historic food market. Back in the kitchen, she shares her recipe for a mouth-watering colcannon. S1, Ep3
Mary spends time with a father and daughter team who run a thriving food truck. Then, she stops by a family-run Italian deli that's been in Camden for nearly 40 years. S1, Ep4
Mary begins her culinary exploration of Yorkshire by sampling some classic dishes in the ancient seaport of Whitby. Later, she visits a world-renowned smokehouse. S1, Ep5
Inspired by a visit to the Caledonian Forest in Scotland, Mary makes some hearty meals. She shares her recipes for a warming hotpot and a tasty puff pastry tart. S1, Ep6
Special Occasions. Dame Mary Berry joins caterers at a wedding and shares her tasty celebration recipes. They include an elegant avocado, beetroot and prawn stack. S1, Ep1
Memories. Dame Mary Berry rediscovers Bristol, home to some special memories. She shares delicious dishes from shakshuka to pear and blueberry galette. S1, Ep2
Team Favourites. Mary is in Birmingham, where she wins over the England players at Edgbaston with her cricket tea. Dishes include hot smoked salmon and jumbo lentil rolls. S1, Ep3
Coastal Delights. Mary explores the historic Jurassic Coast, home of fond childhood memories. She joins a scallop diver and makes delicious dishes including classic moules mariniere. S1, Ep4
Gourmet Garage. Adam seeks out Singapore's secret eats, including chilli crab at a hard-to-find restaurant and char siu at a speakeasy hidden beneath a ramen shop. S2, Ep10
Riverfront Hideaways. Adam eats like a local in Bangkok, where he finds hidden restaurants serving spicy curries and traditional boat noodles served in a locals-only floating market. S2, Ep11
Parma. Adam's in Parma tasting iconic foods named after the city, including tortelli di Parma, prosciutto and a local cake called la torta Duchess di Parma. S1, Ep3
Venice. Adam is in Venice to taste dishes that are not only named after it but imbibe the soul of the city, from a seafood pasta to the original tiramisu. S1, Ep4
Whole Lotta Comfort. Guy Fieri dives into hearty helpings of comfort food. He starts with an eatery that serves up Southern seafood and fried chicken in Atlanta. S29, Ep12
Mega Meat And Sweet Treats. Guy Fieri dives into meat and a little bit of sweet. In Atlanta, a Korean-taqueria serves up unique flavours in their chicken tacos and bulgogi fries. S29, Ep16
Not Your Everyday Eats. Guy Fieri hits the road for out-of-the-ordinary eats. He starts with fried chicken bao in Chico and ends with a duck banh mi and sweet potato lasagne. S29, Ep20
All Kinds Of Comfort. Guy dives into comfort cooking. In Phoenix he finds a funky joint stacking up barbecue fries, and in Boulder there's a pizza place loading up the pies. S28, Ep4
East Coast, West Coast. Guy hits both coasts for tasty dishes. In California, he grabs spicy pork and plantains and visits a bakery-restaurant serving up meatloaf in North Carolina. S28, Ep12
Italian, Hawaiian And Colombian. Guy Fieri tries poke and island specialties in Hawaii and homemade pasta in California. In Miami, a Latin joint serves up tasty Colombian specialities. S28, Ep13
